</title>
<subSubSection id="BD58054720949B0D4AE9F1BF1CD70151" pageId="null" pageNumber="209" type="description">
<paragraph id="D42778A0C9D1CE47EA6F84CAB0775F77" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">
1 
<normalizedToken id="BE58D52F2529DBA91E203EE3C1095599" originalValue="jährig" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">jaehrig</normalizedToken>
; 10-30 cm hoch. Krone 0,4-0,5 cm lang (ohne Sporn), 
<emphasis id="7C0A0585C7118693824053F766FD1349" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">
hellgelb, mit fein und violett gestreifter 
<normalizedToken id="CD61B3E8EB1486EF5102BEBF76D9DA83" originalValue="Röhre" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">Roehre</normalizedToken>
und Oberlippe; Sporn kaum so lang wie die 
<normalizedToken id="1D0AB80DD80BF4111FBCC737E32F0C7B" originalValue="übrige" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">uebrige</normalizedToken>
Krone, fast gerade. Samen etwa 2 mm im Durchmesser; sonst wie 
<taxonomicName id="B0F7B5BD15BA1D853FB86F7283A6264C" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Linaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="null" pageNumber="209" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arvensis">
<authorityName id="25F6A4D6017C45E427E96341B074F2FA" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">L.</authorityName>
arvensis
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(Nr. 6). - 
<normalizedToken id="6614E5338D0F4840EC215580F2E4D048" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9CEC737197AA0CB50D7E8BFBC4B74430" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis id="2854CDA95ED7D534DF1FB935F98D491E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">Zytologische Angaben.</emphasis>
Keine Untersuchungen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="27161987F9D5D7A251712992F69AA736" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis id="128E2757AF754EC33595B7A54E5A6938" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin. 
<normalizedToken id="C367FFF43BAC27B0F1ACF1A5AF03FBD6" originalValue="Ähnlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">Aehnlich</normalizedToken>
wie bei 
<taxonomicName id="5CE2C5B3C757B5AE2E1B584D53E3CE88" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Linaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="null" pageNumber="209" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arvensis">
<emphasis id="DD3DD2B769E662BE3AFDA5A252FD5D43" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">
<authorityName id="7D3F293C89F1272ECC699868317D6283" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">L.</authorityName>
arvensis
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 6).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9BFF7CD356E5AF02333AD74322E591A1" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis id="AF5855A3E34C781067741CD037FDA166" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">
Verbreitung. 
<normalizedToken id="94B4110D1C6DE005109304288BF79F46" originalValue="Südeuropäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">Suedeuropaeische</normalizedToken>
Pflanze:
</emphasis>
Iberische Halbinsel, 
<normalizedToken id="A913CD62F92A0DD337397B9C2F487BC2" originalValue="Südfrankreich" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">Suedfrankreich</normalizedToken>
, Italien, Balkanhalbinsel; in Mitteleuropa gelegentlich eingeschleppt. - Im Gebiet: Savoyen (Maurienne, 
<normalizedToken id="4282A08ABF77DE23732119A3292780CB" originalValue="südwestlicher" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">suedwestlicher</normalizedToken>
Teil), 
<normalizedToken id="8062D3AC2CBF7ED037474E4D69B7EB43" originalValue="südliches" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">suedliches</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="EB2B405CA311319455A2B19BF04B30D3" originalValue="Dép" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">Dep</normalizedToken>
. Ain, 
<normalizedToken id="079C55C939FBC25BF2F37DAEBA4D93C7" originalValue="Dép" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">Dep</normalizedToken>
. Doubs (unteres 
<normalizedToken id="D479BEEDB75299F0EA6C999948A786A5" originalValue="Vallée" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">Vallee</normalizedToken>
de la Loue), sonst selten eingeschleppt (z. B. Genf, Aostatal, Val 
<normalizedToken id="25441CD00169F9F31048784FAACC09AE" originalValue="d’Ossola" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">d'Ossola</normalizedToken>
) und 
<normalizedToken id="EF9FCA489164DB45D99274F907BA9C7E" originalValue="unbeständig" pageId="null" pageNumber="209">unbestaendig</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
